1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:03,533
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,067
Good day, Sir!

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:11,833
What is this update
you are talking about?

4
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:15,300
We believe the watch
belongs to the arsonist.

5
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,600
Have you identified who owns it?

6
00:00:17,733 --> 00:00:19,100
Very well known.

7
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:22,733
Did you mention anything
to Edward about what you know?

8
00:00:22,867 --> 00:00:24,267
He is already suspicious.

9
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,133
Mom, if I were Edward,

10
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:28,700
I would rather know
the real reason

11
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:31,033
why his father treats us
that way.

12
00:00:31,167 --> 00:00:33,233
Mom, that's torture for him.

13
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:36,467
The truth is...

14
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,300
Dad.

15
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:39,500
Edward Torrecampo,

16
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:40,900
you have a warrant of arrest.

17
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:42,967
You are under arrest for arson.

18
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:46,000
Don't take my father away!

19
00:00:46,133 --> 00:00:48,133
Ashley, don't worry about me.

20
00:00:48,267 --> 00:00:50,467
- Okay?
- No!

21
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,300
You're a monster!

22
00:00:53,433 --> 00:00:57,600
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

23
00:01:37,867 --> 00:01:40,600
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

24
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:43,133
They really invited
a lot of people.

25
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:47,733
Mom said the more prayers
for Ashley, the better.

26
00:01:47,867 --> 00:01:51,000
So, at this point, we will
accept all kinds of help.

27
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,333
Even from them.

28
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:54,500
Ash.

29
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:57,100
Guess what?

30
00:01:57,233 --> 00:01:58,667
I invited some of our friends.

31
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,700
Everyone's here to support you.

32
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,800
Uncle Edward, I'll escort Ash.

33
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:07,367
Let's go.

34
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:10,333
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:02:12,100 --> 00:02:15,500
Hey, why does it feel awkward
between you two?

36
00:02:15,667 --> 00:02:17,367
Is everything okay?

37
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:18,333
Yeah.

38
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:19,433
Everything's fine.

39
00:02:19,567 --> 00:02:20,667
Right, Ash?

40
00:02:23,367 --> 00:02:25,733
Grandchildren, come here.

41
00:02:25,867 --> 00:02:27,600
Come on.

42
00:02:27,733 --> 00:02:29,333
Father, can we start now

43
00:02:29,467 --> 00:02:32,033
since we only have three hours
allotted for my grandchild?

44
00:02:32,167 --> 00:02:33,233
Okay, great.

45
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:35,133
Let's begin the mass.

46
00:02:35,267 --> 00:02:39,667
And I hope we are more at peace
this time.

47
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,000
Can we do that?

48
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:43,767
Good day, Sir.

49
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,767
Good day. Please sit.

50
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:54,000
What is this update
you mentioned?

51
00:02:54,133 --> 00:02:56,600
One of our men caught someone.

52
00:02:56,733 --> 00:03:00,900
The guy admitted that he stole
from your burned house.

53
00:03:01,033 --> 00:03:02,667
What items?

54
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,800
Among the items he stole...

55
00:03:05,933 --> 00:03:07,967
was an expensive watch.

56
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:14,233
According to him, he found it
beside the kerosene containers

57
00:03:14,367 --> 00:03:16,600
where the fire started.

58
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:19,867
That is why we believe

59
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,033
the watch belongs
to the arsonist.

60
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,233
Wait.

61
00:03:23,367 --> 00:03:28,000
It's impossible for Yolly
to own an expensive watch.

62
00:03:29,033 --> 00:03:31,333
Could she have stolen it
from us?

63
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:34,967
If she stole it,

64
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:36,700
why would she leave it behind?

65
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:40,233
Here it is, Sir.

66
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:52,767
Are you saying it's possible
that the one who burned my house

67
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:56,100
is the owner of this watch?

68
00:03:56,267 --> 00:03:57,767
Yes.

69
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:00,333
Do you recognize who owns it?

70
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:02,967
Yes.

71
00:04:03,100 --> 00:04:04,467
Very well known.

72
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:07,467
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

73
00:04:10,167 --> 00:04:12,367
Go in peace.

74
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:14,067
In the name of the Father,

75
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,300
the Son,

76
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:17,667
and the Holy Spirit.

77
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:19,467
- Amen.
- Amen.

78
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,233
Thank you, Father.

79
00:04:23,267 --> 00:04:26,167
Let's eat. Please, let's eat.

80
00:04:26,300 --> 00:04:27,767
Enjoy the food.

81
00:04:27,933 --> 00:04:29,833
I'll get you some food.

82
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,967
Ash, do you want me
to get you food?

83
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:40,733
Not too salty, not too fatty,
right?

84
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:42,067
It's okay.

85
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,033
I don't have an appetite.

86
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:47,100
Probably because
of my medication.

87
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:49,133
All right, I'll just get you
some cake.

88
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:51,333
I'll be back.

89
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:53,567
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:04:55,433 --> 00:05:00,167
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

91
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:08,133
<i> You guys eat. Enjoy the food.</i>

92
00:06:02,900 --> 00:06:03,967
My child.

93
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,567
There's baked mac.

94
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,800
Do you want some?

95
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,067
Hey.

96
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,767
Why are you crying?

97
00:06:11,900 --> 00:06:13,133
Nothing.

98
00:06:13,267 --> 00:06:15,133
My eyes are just irritated.

99
00:06:25,767 --> 00:06:27,333
She should have been
the one sick.

100
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:30,467
She should be the one
being prayed over.

101
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,800
You should be the one walking.

102
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:35,400
You should be the one
without worries.

103
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,133
Sorry, Mom, I have to go.

104
00:06:39,267 --> 00:06:40,867
Wait.

105
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,367
Stay here, my child.

106
00:06:42,533 --> 00:06:43,500
Please.

107
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,833
Just for a moment.

108
00:07:01,967 --> 00:07:03,400
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

109
00:07:04,667 --> 00:07:06,000
Thea, wait.

110
00:07:06,133 --> 00:07:08,400
Can I talk to you?

111
00:07:08,533 --> 00:07:11,400
Marj, I'm not in the mood
to pretend.

112
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:13,500
Just stay away from me.

113
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:16,600
I might forget that
mass just ended.

114
00:07:16,767 --> 00:07:18,633
Thea, please.

115
00:07:18,767 --> 00:07:21,267
For the children's sake.

116
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,233
Ash?

117
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,767
Ash, why did you leave?

118
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,500
I got you a slice of cake.

119
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:28,933
You can keep it.

120
00:07:29,067 --> 00:07:30,333
I'm not in the mood.

121
00:07:31,933 --> 00:07:33,933
Wait, Ash, are you mad at me?

122
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:36,467
What?

123
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,967
Because it feels like
you're avoiding me.

124
00:07:40,100 --> 00:07:41,267
If you're mad at me...

125
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,500
I'm not mad at you, okay?

126
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,267
But lately, I'm starting
to realize

127
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:49,467
that maybe my decision
to donate to you was wrong.

128
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,633
Let's stop fighting.

129
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:56,233
Let's forget what happened.

130
00:07:56,367 --> 00:07:58,833
We've punished each other
enough.

131
00:07:58,967 --> 00:08:00,567
And that's enough.

132
00:08:02,667 --> 00:08:05,133
What punishment did you get?

133
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:06,867
You and Paolo are fine.

134
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,433
Your child is healthy.

135
00:08:09,700 --> 00:08:12,000
You're getting back
on your feet.

136
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:13,667
But I'm still down.

137
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,100
I feel like I'm being punished

138
00:08:16,233 --> 00:08:18,300
because of what happened
to Ashley.

139
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:21,333
I wanted to help you, Jasmine.

140
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,600
But I didn't expect this.

141
00:08:26,167 --> 00:08:27,167
I don't want to be
in a wheelchair

142
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,667
for the rest of my life.

143
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,267
I don't want that.

144
00:08:31,533 --> 00:08:35,267
I wish I hadn't tried
to be your savior.

145
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:39,900
Then maybe I wouldn't be
suffering now!

146
00:08:40,033 --> 00:08:43,467
Thea, you don't have
to face this alone.

147
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,767
Paolo and I are here.

148
00:08:44,900 --> 00:08:48,600
We're willing to help.

149
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,333
Marj, that's not what I need.

150
00:08:51,467 --> 00:08:56,667
What I want is for you to pay
for what you did to Ashley.

151
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:58,467
Even if Edward is against it,

152
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,600
I will continue the case
against you.

153
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:04,500
I don't want you to suffer
either, Ash, believe me.

154
00:09:04,633 --> 00:09:07,233
I know and I'm not blaming you!

155
00:09:07,367 --> 00:09:11,000
You didn't force me.

156
00:09:11,133 --> 00:09:13,267
What I'm trying to say is

157
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:17,300
if I could go back
to that moment,

158
00:09:17,433 --> 00:09:19,367
maybe I might choose
differently.

159
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:22,433
I don't want to experience this
anymore!

160
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:24,000
It's so hard!

161
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:25,633
[SOBBING]

162
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:28,133
I'm sorry, Ash.

163
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,733
Just leave me alone!

164
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,700
Leave!

165
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:33,733
Thea.

166
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:37,533
Don't expect that
we'll ever be okay again.

167
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:40,933
Stop it with your fake niceness.

168
00:09:41,967 --> 00:09:43,933
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:51,200
Just leave me alone.

170
00:09:52,867 --> 00:09:55,333
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

171
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:58,500
[SOBBING]

172
00:09:58,633 --> 00:10:01,967
[DRAMATIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

173
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:10,567
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

174
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:19,767
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

175
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:24,300
Marj.

176
00:10:27,033 --> 00:10:30,467
Did you mention anything
to Edward about what you know?

177
00:10:31,967 --> 00:10:33,633
No, Mom.

178
00:10:33,767 --> 00:10:36,167
But he is already suspicious.

179
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:37,033
What?

180
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:40,500
He said he asked you,

181
00:10:40,633 --> 00:10:43,300
but he knows you are not telling
the truth.

182
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:47,733
Mom, I think it's time
you tell him already.

183
00:10:47,867 --> 00:10:48,867
How can I?

184
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:52,300
Am I supposed to add
to his problems?

185
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:54,133
Mom, if I were Edward,

186
00:10:54,267 --> 00:10:56,733
I would rather know
the real reason

187
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:58,733
why my father treats me that way

188
00:11:00,167 --> 00:11:04,633
than thinking every day
about what I did wrong

189
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:07,367
and why he treats me like that.

190
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:09,400
Mom, that's torture for him.

191
00:11:10,467 --> 00:11:12,300
I hope you understand that.

192
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:20,467
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

193
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:36,333
Let me guess.

194
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:38,133
Jas told on me, right?

195
00:11:39,233 --> 00:11:41,600
Go on, tell me I'm a bad person.

196
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,900
You're not a bad person, Ash.

197
00:11:46,600 --> 00:11:48,333
I know you're extremely
frustrated

198
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:50,333
because of everything
that's happening.

199
00:11:50,467 --> 00:11:52,533
And that's why you said
those things to Jas.

200
00:11:55,633 --> 00:11:57,333
You know what, Xander?

201
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:59,900
Why don't you just teach Jas
how to skateboard instead?

202
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,767
Take her instead to the concert.

203
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,400
She's the one who's okay now.

204
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:07,433
She's the one who can walk.

205
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:11,200
She's the one
who doesn't need assistance.

206
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:13,433
- Ashley.
- Unlike me.

207
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:16,800
I'm high maintenance.

208
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,267
So, pick her instead.

209
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:21,867
Don't pick me, Xander.

210
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:25,333
Because there's a chance
I might never walk again.

211
00:12:25,467 --> 00:12:27,200
I don't care about that, Ash.

212
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:28,667
But I do!

213
00:12:29,733 --> 00:12:32,133
I do care about it, Xander.

214
00:12:32,267 --> 00:12:36,333
I don't want the day to come
when you regret choosing me.

215
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:39,233
I don't want you

216
00:12:39,367 --> 00:12:42,800
to get fed up
because I'm a burden.

217
00:12:42,933 --> 00:12:46,433
So that's the reason
you're rejecting me?

218
00:12:46,567 --> 00:12:48,433
Isn't that unfair?

219
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:51,067
You haven't even given me
a chance, Ashley.

220
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:53,600
I think it's for the best.

221
00:12:53,733 --> 00:12:55,400
I'm so sorry, Xander.

222
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:00,933
["KATOTOHANAN" THEME MUSIC
PLAYING]

223
00:13:11,133 --> 00:13:12,433
Excuse me.

224
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:19,367
Edward, can we talk?

225
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,200
Are you avoiding me?

226
00:13:23,167 --> 00:13:24,700
Edward, please.

227
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:25,767
Please.

228
00:13:28,067 --> 00:13:29,333
You want to know the truth?

229
00:13:31,467 --> 00:13:33,500
I'm upset with you

230
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:35,600
because I feel like you're
hiding something from me.

231
00:13:36,767 --> 00:13:39,067
Mom, aren't you on my side?

232
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,267
Why do I feel that
you're hiding the truth

233
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,767
about what Dad said

234
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,333
about what I don't know?

235
00:13:49,167 --> 00:13:50,867
The truth is...

236
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,333
Dad.

237
00:13:52,467 --> 00:13:53,633
You changed your mind.

238
00:13:55,933 --> 00:13:57,167
Dad!

239
00:13:57,300 --> 00:13:58,267
Dad.

240
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,900
I wasn't expecting you.

241
00:14:06,633 --> 00:14:07,900
That's yours.

242
00:14:08,033 --> 00:14:09,067
Am I right?

243
00:14:10,133 --> 00:14:12,100
Yes, this is mine.

244
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:14,133
I thought it was lost
in the fire.

245
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:17,100
It was lost.

246
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:18,267
In the fire.

247
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,300
In the fire that you caused.

248
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:23,200
You're the arsonist!

249
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:26,267
What?

250
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,367
What the hell are you saying?

251
00:14:28,533 --> 00:14:32,267
- [INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [BACKGROUND CHATTER]

252
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:40,133
What's happening?

253
00:14:43,167 --> 00:14:45,700
Edward Torrecampo,
you have a warrant of arrest.

254
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:51,933
You are under arrest for arson
for burning your own home.

255
00:14:52,067 --> 00:14:53,233
What?

256
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,600
I didn't do anything like that.

257
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,400
I didn't burn the house!

258
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,567
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

259
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:09,567
[INTENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:14,567
Put the handcuffs on him.

261
00:15:15,300 --> 00:15:16,167
No!

262
00:15:16,300 --> 00:15:18,167
This is ridiculous!
He's your son!

263
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:19,300
What is wrong with you, Greg?

264
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:20,467
Dad.

265
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,700
Wait! Wait!

266
00:15:21,833 --> 00:15:23,233
I didn't burn anything!

267
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:25,567
I don't know anything
about what he's accusing me of!

268
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:27,167
Take him to the station.

269
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:29,133
Let go of my husband!

270
00:15:29,267 --> 00:15:30,233
Dad!

271
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,367
How could you?

272
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:36,467
You're sending your own child
to jail?

273
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:38,333
What kind of parent are you?

274
00:15:38,467 --> 00:15:40,467
Because you're not
my real child!

275
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:45,067
You're Regina's child
by another man.

276
